query: Can you show me the syllabus for CMPSC 311 (SP25)?

document.title: Syllabus for CMPSC 311 (SP25)
document.content: Instructor Information Dr. Suman Saha Assistant Teaching Professor Department of Computer Science and Engineering Email: szs339@psu.edu Teaching Assistants • MD Amit Hasan Arovi • Ashwin Senthil Arumugam • Md Rafi Ur Rashid • Yilu Dong Office Hours Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday Dr. Suman Saha Location: W109F Westgate Building 9:00 AM - 10:00 AM 2:00 PM - 3:00 PM MD Amit Hasan Arovi Location: Zoom Online 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM 11:00 AM - 12:00 PM Ashwin Senthil Arumugam Location: Zoom Online 11:00 AM - 12:00 PM Md Rafi Ur Rashid Location: 300W building 11:00 AM - 12:00 PM Yilu Dong Location: 300W building 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM Course Objectives: This course explores intro sys prog concepts and methodologies. Students will gain hands-on experience through lectures, programming assignments, and projects. Grading Activity Percentage Course Projects 50% Midterm Exams 30% Final Exam 20% Academic Integrity Statement The course projects are to be carried out individually. Students are explicitly not allowed to share information, source code, or even discuss the contents of the projects. Any violation of this policy will be considered cheating and will result in the student receiving an 'F' grade for the project. Lateness Policy Lab assignments are assessed a 10% per day late penalty, up to a maximum of three days after which a zero grade will be given.

document.content: Environmental Geology is an introduction to Earth's systems and environmental challenges. This course explores current issues in earth science and their implications for the future. The syllabus below is for your convenience. It contains all of the due dates for the assignments, but it does not contain the policies or other details about the course. Earth 105 Complete Syllabus Please use the Home page to see the course structure, links, and instructions for all of the assignments.
